isEmpty

headTimePassed

public boolean headTimePassed(long time)
Determine if current time is past (or equal) to update time for node at the head of the list (the earliest update in list).

Parameters:
time - current system time
Returns:
true if current time greater than (or equal) update time for head node

removeHead

public void removeHead()
Remove timer node at head of list.

popHead

public TimerNode popHead()
Pop node from head of list. If monitor has not reached end of duration, set next update time for node, and re-insert into list. If monitor has reached end of duration, remove from list.

Returns:
former head of list, if end of duration has been reached, null otherwise

insert

public TimerNode insert(int monitorId,
                        long period,
                        Messenger callback,
                        long duration)
Insert a new periodic monitor into timer list. Creates new TimerNode and inserts it in sorted order based on next update time.

Parameters:
monitorId - unique id of monitor
period - time between updates in milliseconds
callback - client handler to handle update messages
duration - total duration to monitor metric, in milliseconds
Returns:
newly created TimerNode inserted into list

insertNode

protected void insertNode(TimerNode tnode)
Insert TimerNode into list. Used by EavesdropList subclass. Key is equivalent to period for opportunistic monitor nodes.

Parameters:
tnode - TimerNode to insert in monitor list

remove

Remove periodic monitor which was registered using this message handler.

monitorId - unique id of monitor
Returns:
node that was removed if match was found, null otherwise
